-- Telecom NZ, Vodafone Make Joint Bid For Rural Broadband Project
-- B y   C h r i s   B o u r k e
-- 2010-11-11T19:41:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-11/telecom-corp-vodafone-make-joint-bid-for-new-zealand-rural-broadband-plan.html
Telecom Corp. of New Zealand and
Vodafone Group Plc have submitted a joint proposal to build an
open access broadband network in New Zealand’s rural areas,
according to a statement today.  The proposal is the companies’ joint response to the
government’s Rural Broadband Initiative, the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
